00:00.376 --> 00:01.491
So here's what you missed
on <i>Glee...</i>

00:01.502 --> 00:03.052
I needed you around,
and you weren't there.

00:03.070 --> 00:04.387
<i>Blaine cheated on Kurt</i>
<i>and they broke up,</i>

00:04.405 --> 00:06.239
<i>and Rachel and Finn</i>
<i>broke up, too, and Finn</i>

00:06.273 --> 00:08.491
<i>has no idea what he wants to
do with his life.</i> We're done.

00:08.525 --> 00:09.993
<i>Jake has his eye on Marley,</i>

00:10.027 --> 00:11.894
<i>which Kitty's</i>
<i>really not happy about,</i>

00:11.912 --> 00:13.162
<i>and Emma's not sure she wants</i>
<i>to leave McKinley</i>

00:13.197 --> 00:14.998
<i>to go to Washington with Will.</i>

00:15.032 --> 00:17.083
<i>And that's what</i>
<i>you missed on</i> Glee.

00:23.707 --> 00:25.741
Why do I always feel
so at home in a tire shop?

00:25.759 --> 00:28.011
That was a joke.
What do you want, Artie?

00:28.045 --> 00:29.245
I got a lot of work to do.

00:29.263 --> 00:30.413
I just wanted
to check in on you.

00:30.431 --> 00:31.547
You've had
a rough couple of months,

00:31.581 --> 00:32.747
and I thought maybe
you could use a friend.

00:32.766 --> 00:33.850
It's not that bad.

00:33.884 --> 00:35.418
I just embarrassed myself
out of the army,

00:35.436 --> 00:37.086
lost Rachel completely,

00:37.104 --> 00:39.588
and now I'm back in my hometown
working in a tire shop.

00:39.607 --> 00:41.257
Figure maybe my luck
will change soon

00:41.275 --> 00:42.358
and one of the lifts will break,

00:42.393 --> 00:43.592
and I'll get crushed by a car.

00:44.795 --> 00:47.530
I'm sorry, Artie.

00:47.564 --> 00:49.065
I appreciate what you're
doing; You're a great friend.

00:49.099 --> 00:50.400
I'm just kind of sitting
back and looking

00:50.434 --> 00:52.101
at the next 60
years of my life.

00:52.119 --> 00:53.602
It just sort of makes me
want to puke.

00:53.621 --> 00:55.288
But it is what it is.

00:55.322 --> 00:56.439
Do you remember what I said

00:56.457 --> 00:58.041
when I dedicated that song
to you last year?

00:58.075 --> 01:00.410
That you were
my friend, my hero.

01:00.444 --> 01:02.245
I'm not gonna let you bury
yourself in self-pity, Finn.

01:02.279 --> 01:03.630
You're better than that.

01:03.664 --> 01:05.548
You know, I've heard that
a lot all my life, Artie.

01:05.582 --> 01:07.550
That I'm better
than I think I am.

01:07.584 --> 01:09.452
Well, look around.

01:09.470 --> 01:10.920
Maybe I'm not.
You just lost

01:10.954 --> 01:12.788
