26:28.399 --> 26:30.017
but I like Unique for it.

26:30.068 --> 26:31.134
He wants it so badly.

26:31.152 --> 26:32.769
He's the best singer, too.

26:32.803 --> 26:35.639
So, we cast a brunette
as Sandy and a guy as Rizzo.

26:35.657 --> 26:37.658
Who's directing this, Julie Taymor?
Think about how cool

26:37.692 --> 26:39.476
it would be to do something
really different.

26:39.494 --> 26:41.328
Though I don't agree
with your choices,

26:41.362 --> 26:43.447
I appreciate your passion.

26:43.481 --> 26:45.999
It's nice to have
the old Finn back.

26:46.034 --> 26:47.618
Sue:
Finn Hudson?

26:47.652 --> 26:50.537
In Principal Figgins'
office now.

26:51.923 --> 26:54.291
Now, fatty!
(Bell ringing)

26:54.325 --> 26:56.126
The twin idiots seated
before you are poised

26:56.160 --> 26:59.329
to cast the she-male-fabulous
Unique Adams

26:59.347 --> 27:00.848
as Rizzo in <i>Grease;</i>

27:00.882 --> 27:02.649
The already overly sexualized
minstrel show

27:02.684 --> 27:06.687
featuring teen pregnancy
and the ridiculously unnecessary

27:06.721 --> 27:08.305
lubrication of lightning.

27:08.339 --> 27:10.807
If they succeed,
they will set a legal precedent

27:10.841 --> 27:13.477
that will clear the way
for Unique to become a Cheerio!

27:13.511 --> 27:16.480
In the very year that I am set
to notch my 1,000th

27:16.514 --> 27:19.316
tournament victory
and become the winningest coach

27:19.350 --> 27:21.034
in cheerleading history.

27:21.069 --> 27:23.320
Wait. When did Unique say
he wanted to be a Cheerio!?

27:23.354 --> 27:24.488
Sue, I don't understand.

27:24.522 --> 27:26.490
Unique Adams is nothing more

27:26.524 --> 27:28.525
than an attractive,
buxom young woman

27:28.543 --> 27:31.528
who's got it going on
in all the right places.

27:31.546 --> 27:32.746
She's a brick house, Sue!

27:32.797 --> 27:35.165
Uh, Principal Figgins,
Sue's right about that.

27:35.199 --> 27:37.584
Unique is definitely a guy.

27:37.635 --> 27:39.586
What? I don't see
what the big deal is.

27:39.637 --> 27:41.889
If Unique identifies as a girl
and dresses

27:41.923 --> 27:44.341
as a girl, she should be allowed
to play one onstage.

27:44.375 --> 27:46.876
Cross-gendered casting
is as old as theater itself.

27:46.895 --> 27:49.713
In Shakespeare's time, all the
female roles were played by men.

27:49.731 --> 27:50.681
There's no way that's true.

27:50.715 --> 27:52.015
In the last few years,

27:52.050 --> 27:53.233
McKinley's become
the kind of place

27:53.268 --> 27:55.152
where all kinds of outcasts
can feel free

27:55.186 --> 27:58.021
to follow their dreams.
I don't think that should change

27:58.055 --> 27:59.907
just because
Coach Sylvester's a bigot.

27:59.941 --> 28:02.826
You know, I'd think twice
about calling someone a bigot

28:02.860 --> 28:05.329
who's had gay Cheerios!, both
male and female on her squad,

28:05.363 --> 28:07.664
and who resigned her post
as principal in protest

28:07.699 --> 28:09.333
because this school
wasn't doing enough

28:09.367 --> 28:11.335
to protect a gay student
from being bullied!

28:11.369 --> 28:13.236
But you do have a point there,
mashed potato pants.

28:13.254 --> 28:14.705
We've become somewhat of a

28:14.739 --> 28:17.240
progressive bubble here at
McKinley High, and I think

28:17.258 --> 28:19.676
that's due to the fact
that the Glee Club is being run

28:19.711 --> 28:21.745
by a strange, weepy man-child
who has lotion

28:21.763 --> 28:23.547
in his hair,
but no adult friends.

28:23.581 --> 28:24.765
We live in Ohio.

28:24.799 --> 28:27.434
And if you choose to cast Rizzo
with a naive,

28:27.468 --> 28:28.769
gender-confused boy

28:28.803 --> 28:32.773
in a dress,
I guarantee you someone...

28:32.807 --> 28:35.275
Is going to raise
a very public stink about it,

28:35.310 --> 28:37.444
and I don't think that's fair.

28:37.478 --> 28:40.063
Don't put this kid in danger
because you want to make

28:40.097 --> 28:43.400
some grand gesture
about how open-minded you are.

28:43.434 --> 28:45.953
William, I spent the last year

28:45.987 --> 28:48.104
stifling my natural hatred
for you and helping you win

28:48.122 --> 28:50.607
a Glee Club
national championship.

28:50.625 --> 28:52.376
Now is your moment
to pay me back by putting

28:52.410 --> 28:54.277
a stop to this
so I don't have to.

28:54.295 --> 28:55.579
It's not my call, Sue.

28:55.613 --> 28:57.297
Finn and Artie are running
the musical this year,

28:57.332 --> 28:58.615
and I trust them implicitly.

28:58.633 --> 29:00.884
Enough! With all due respect,

29:00.918 --> 29:02.469
this is none of your business.

29:02.503 --> 29:04.972
I'm the director.
It's my decision.

29:05.006 --> 29:07.457
William, maybe you need to
remind chubby-wan-Kenobi

29:07.475 --> 29:10.260
of the daily nightmare that is
borne of being my enemy.

29:10.294 --> 29:11.645
You can't threaten me, Sue.

29:11.679 --> 29:14.964
I've already lost my girlfriend,
my future, my pride.

29:14.983 --> 29:16.466
I've nothing more to lose.

29:16.484 --> 29:18.935
I'm casting Unique,
and that's all there is to it.

29:18.969 --> 29:22.105
And you know, I thought
that you would have known more

29:22.139 --> 29:24.241
about being an underdog after
you helped us win nationals

29:24.275 --> 29:25.942
and had a retarded baby,
but you...

29:28.696 --> 29:31.248
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to say that.

29:31.282 --> 29:34.951
That... that was the wrong word
to use. I apologize.

29:44.379 --> 29:46.496
(School bell ringing)

29:49.537 --> 29:52.872
You look more crooked
than Joe Theismann's leg.

29:52.906 --> 29:54.791
It's just these places that the
realtor in Washington sent us.

29:54.842 --> 29:55.792
They all have carpeting.

29:55.843 --> 29:56.909
You know how many germs

29:56.927 --> 29:58.044
and bugs and fluids
live in carpeting?

29:58.078 --> 29:59.179
Call Stanley Steemer.

29:59.213 --> 30:00.913
Cleaned carpets
that don't dry properly

30:00.931 --> 30:03.216
can create kawasaki syndrome.

30:03.250 --> 30:07.520
You know what the worst thing
you can do in a relationship is?

30:07.555 --> 30:09.856
Besides hitting, of course?
Lie.

30:09.890 --> 30:12.108
You don't want to go
with Will to Washington.

30:12.143 --> 30:14.110
I saw it in your face
when you told him you would.

30:14.145 --> 30:16.863
I have reservations; That is
much different from lying.

30:16.897 --> 30:18.281
You know what they say
about reservations?

30:18.315 --> 30:20.700
They won't seat you
till the whole party's there.

30:20.735 --> 30:22.769
Dishonesty eats away
at a marriage.

30:22.787 --> 30:24.070
You have to tell him
you don't want to go.

30:24.104 --> 30:26.289
I can't. I can't get in the way
of his dreams.

30:26.323 --> 30:27.540
That's what Terri did.

30:27.575 --> 30:31.294
Pumpkin, Will loves you

30:31.328 --> 30:34.080
like a farmer loves
his blue ribbon pig.

30:34.114 --> 30:37.584
He'll understand.

30:37.618 --> 30:41.588
I'm going. It's decided.

30:41.622 --> 30:43.757
Then you'd better find
something to get excited about

30:43.791 --> 30:45.091
doing down there besides him.

30:45.125 --> 30:47.477
You know I love Will,
but I think you've spent

30:47.511 --> 30:50.063
so much time working on being
his girl that you forgot

30:50.097 --> 30:52.982
that the reason he's so into you
is because of all the things

30:53.017 --> 30:54.934
you are <i>besides</i> that.

30:59.824 --> 31:03.076
(School bell ringing) I've been
trying to see you since I got here,

31:03.110 --> 31:05.812
but every time I get
near you, you disappear.

31:05.830 --> 31:07.497
I was fine with our breakup.

31:07.531 --> 31:09.616
Out of sight, out of mind.
But maybe you

31:09.650 --> 31:11.751
could have called and asked
if I could handle you

31:11.786 --> 31:13.169
choreographing
the school musical!

31:13.204 --> 31:15.171
I'm sorry. Artie called me.

31:15.206 --> 31:17.824
It seemed like a fun idea.
I didn't think you'd be upset.

31:17.842 --> 31:19.626
Neither did I!

31:19.660 --> 31:21.594
I know this is weird.
It's weird for me, too,

31:21.629 --> 31:22.846
but if that's
what's stopping you

31:22.880 --> 31:24.163
from auditioning for <i>Grease,</i>

31:24.181 --> 31:26.015
then we have to
make this not weird.

31:26.050 --> 31:27.834
There are still some
good parts left.

31:27.852 --> 31:29.602
I'm sorry, I can't.

31:29.637 --> 31:32.355
We could use you.
You're so talented.

31:32.389 --> 31:35.391
I'm sorry. You're gonna have
to survive without my talent.

31:36.510 --> 31:37.811
(Sighs)

31:37.845 --> 31:39.779
(School bell ringing)

31:39.814 --> 31:42.348
All right! You guys
killed your auditions,

31:42.366 --> 31:46.853
but there can only be one Sandy
and there can only be one Danny.

31:46.871 --> 31:48.855
The heart of <i>Grease</i>
is the Danny-Sandy romance.

31:48.873 --> 31:51.023
This callback is all
about the chemistry.

31:51.041 --> 31:54.377
We want to see how well you play
off each other. Is there heat?

31:54.411 --> 31:56.996
Finn: We also want to see how
you sing and dance '50s-stye.

31:57.030 --> 31:59.215
That's why we gave you the
audition song ahead of time.

31:59.250 --> 32:01.000
I don't really read
music, so...

32:01.035 --> 32:02.802
Mike:
It's okay.

32:02.837 --> 32:05.221
Mercedes and I will get you started.
Kitty: Start away.

32:05.256 --> 32:07.807
Everyone knows Kitty cat's
gonna finish it.

32:07.842 --> 32:09.976
Oh, you have a lot
of attitude, little girl.

32:10.010 --> 32:13.880
Let's see if you have the stuff
to back it up. Hit it.

32:13.898 --> 32:16.215
(Sha na na's
"born to hand-jive" plays)

