Gentlemen?

32:52.085 --> 32:53.603
♪ While chopping wood

32:53.637 --> 32:56.422
♪ I moved my legs

32:56.440 --> 33:00.026
♪ and they saw me dancing
when I gathered eggs ♪

33:00.060 --> 33:01.895
♪ the townfolk clapped,
I was only five ♪

33:01.929 --> 33:03.112
♪ he'll out-dance 'em all

33:03.147 --> 33:05.732
♪ he was born to hand-jive

33:18.829 --> 33:21.280
♪ oh yeah, yeah, yeah...

33:21.298 --> 33:23.449
♪ Everybody... Artie: Break it up.
Break it up.

33:23.467 --> 33:26.252
♪ Born to hand-jive, baby

33:26.286 --> 33:29.973
♪ born to hand-jive,
baby ♪

33:45.272 --> 33:47.073
♪ how low can you go?

33:47.107 --> 33:48.474
♪ How low
can you go? ♪

33:48.492 --> 33:50.827
♪ how low can you go?

33:50.861 --> 33:53.145
♪ How low
can you go? ♪

33:53.163 --> 33:54.447
♪ higher...

33:54.481 --> 33:56.866
♪ Higher

33:56.917 --> 33:58.952
♪ higher...

33:58.986 --> 34:00.954
♪ And higher, yeah

34:00.988 --> 34:04.123
♪ now can you hand-jive, baby?

34:04.157 --> 34:06.759
♪ Oh, can you
hand-jive, baby? ♪

34:06.794 --> 34:08.494
♪ baby ♪ oh yeah

34:08.512 --> 34:10.797
♪ can you hand-jive, baby?
♪ give me hand-jive

34:10.831 --> 34:15.435
♪ oh, can you hand-jive, baby?

34:15.469 --> 34:17.219
♪ Oh yeah ♪ oh yeah

34:17.271 --> 34:19.138
♪ oh yeah ♪ oh yeah yeah

34:19.172 --> 34:21.340
♪ oh yeah ♪ oh yeah

34:21.358 --> 34:23.275
♪ born to hand-jive, oh yeah!

34:23.310 --> 34:25.011
We did good.

34:25.029 --> 34:26.696
(Whooping, laughing)

34:34.212 --> 34:36.614
(School bell ringing)

34:40.402 --> 34:43.286
Hey. I came to talk
to you about the play.

34:44.206 --> 34:45.389
I get it.

34:45.399 --> 34:47.317
I heard about
Coach Sylvester's meltdown.

34:48.619 --> 34:50.436
I want to offer you the part.

34:52.739 --> 34:54.858
but what about Coach Sue?

34:54.891 --> 34:56.458
Well, Coach Sue isn't
directing the play.

34:56.494 --> 34:58.078
I am.

34:58.112 --> 35:01.197
So now all you got to worry
about is getting a curly way

35:01.227 --> 35:03.497
***

35:03.617 --> 35:05.118
and I'll take care of Coach Sue

35:05.152 --> 35:08.238
or anybody else who
might try and st us.

35:08.272 --> 35:10.874
Unique knows the song
and has the wig.

35:10.908 --> 35:12.342
Good.

35:14.762 --> 35:17.063
You okay?

35:17.098 --> 35:19.833
I feel right
the men's locker room.

35:19.867 --> 35:21.634
But I can't go into the girls'.

35:21.669 --> 35:24.988
And I don't feel right
in men's clothing,

35:25.022 --> 35:27.907
but I can't wear
dresses every day.

35:32.630 --> 35:36.082
It's just nice, for once,

35:39.837 --> 35:42.005
yeah, it is.

35:44.658 --> 35:46.343
Well, uh...

35:46.377 --> 35:48.661
(Sniffs)

35:48.679 --> 35:50.296
Before I post the cast list,

35:50.330 --> 35:51.915
I just need to Kat you're ready.

35:51.949 --> 35:53.433
'Cause there's gonna be
a lot of heat on you,

35:53.467 --> 35:55.802
and like I said, I can shield
you from some of it, but...

35:55.836 --> 35:57.303
At the end of the day,
you're gonna be the one

35:57.337 --> 35:58.738
out on that stage.

36:02.460 --> 36:03.877
(School bell ringing)

36:32.539 --> 36:34.891
All right, all right.

37:05.739 --> 37:08.108
(Laughing)

37:15.950 --> 37:17.784
Patty Simcox?

37:18.803 --> 37:20.770
Patty Simcox?

37:20.805 --> 37:22.555
Who the hell is Patty Simcox?

37:24.708 --> 37:25.925
I don't understand.

37:25.943 --> 37:28.061
I pray really hard about this.

37:28.095 --> 37:29.512
Maybe God didn't hear you
because he was busy

37:29.547 --> 37:32.782
helping people with cancer.
Shut it, Avatar.

37:32.817 --> 37:35.084
This is all your fault.
You screwed up "hand -jive."

37:35.086 --> 37:37.287
No, I didn't.
We were both great.

37:37.321 --> 37:39.405
It just didn't work out.

37:39.439 --> 37:40.924
I've been hearing that
a lot lately from you.

37:43.494 --> 37:45.812
Oh. One little thing,
honey boo boo.

37:45.846 --> 37:47.630
I know a good, hot meal
is hard to resist,

37:47.632 --> 37:50.083
especially when you're on
the free lunch program

37:50.117 --> 37:53.286
but remember, the stage always
*** at least ten pounds.

37:53.320 --> 37:55.638
In your case, it's close to 90.

37:55.673 --> 37:56.848
So, when you and your mom,
strawberry hugryake,

37:56.866 --> 37:58.819
are dumpster diving for your costume,

37:58.828 --> 38:01.227
keep on picking till you
find something slimming.

38:01.262 --> 38:03.963
Like a back hefty bag.

38:03.981 --> 38:06.432
Kitty, my baby needs to be fed.

38:37.313 --> 38:39.865
Emma, wow.

38:42.001 --> 38:43.835
Did I forget it's one of
our anniversaries?

38:43.870 --> 38:46.321
What? No.
(Sighs)

38:46.339 --> 38:48.290
Your parents aren't
here, are they?

38:48.324 --> 38:50.125
No no no. No, no.
I just thought I would, um,

38:50.159 --> 38:51.960
challenge myself with
a few new recipes, that's all.

38:51.994 --> 38:53.962
Okay. How many new recipes?

38:53.996 --> 38:56.598
Uh, two or three.
Or seven. Sorry.

38:56.632 --> 38:58.016
If you want, in just a couple
minutes, they'll be ready.

38:58.051 --> 38:59.685
Just let them cool for a second.

38:59.719 --> 39:02.104
Um...,
I just got home early

39:02.138 --> 39:04.272
and I, uh, came across
these cookbooks

39:04.307 --> 39:06.508
my mom got me when I got married
to Carl, and I thought you'd like it.

39:06.526 --> 39:08.510
You know what? I've never
tried these. And I feel like

39:08.528 --> 39:10.812
I do that sometimes, and it's
really not fair. Emma... ma.

39:10.814 --> 39:12.114
Sometimes I need to try...
Emma.

39:12.148 --> 39:14.116
Emma, stop.

39:14.150 --> 39:16.535
Just... whatever it is,

39:16.569 --> 39:18.987
just say it.

39:20.573 --> 39:22.991
I don't want to go to
Washington with you.

39:28.331 --> 39:30.716
Could you just sit down?

39:31.834 --> 39:34.202
Just hear me out.

39:39.041 --> 39:41.209
(Clears throat)
For the past three years,

39:41.227 --> 39:44.012
all I've wanted
was to be your wife.

39:44.046 --> 39:45.731
But then when I rely
stop to think about that,

39:45.765 --> 39:47.232
I have no idea what
that means to me,

39:47.266 --> 39:48.650
to be a wife.

39:48.684 --> 39:50.152
You know? I, um...

39:50.186 --> 39:52.821
I know what it meant to my mom.
It meant, you know,

39:52.855 --> 39:54.523
having supper on the table
when my dad got home.

39:54.557 --> 39:56.858
It meant lots of
"whatever you say, dear"s.

39:56.892 --> 39:58.894
It was heroic doses of
clonopin and chardonnay, and...

39:58.928 --> 40:01.079
That's not the life I want.
I know.

40:01.114 --> 40:03.081
I love you.

40:03.116 --> 40:05.233
I love you, but I love my job.

40:05.268 --> 40:06.585
I love my kids.

40:06.619 --> 40:08.203
I love helping my kids.

40:08.237 --> 40:09.588
I love that you love your job,

40:09.622 --> 40:11.089
and I... I am so
incredibly excited

40:11.124 --> 40:13.508
for this job opportunity
for you, I really am.

40:13.543 --> 40:16.044
But I am terrified

40:16.078 --> 40:17.745
that if I go with you,
I'm gonna resent you.

40:17.764 --> 40:19.247
And then I'm gonna pull away.

40:19.265 --> 40:20.882
I would rather be here,

40:20.916 --> 40:22.750
far from you
but feeling really close,

40:22.769 --> 40:26.087
rather than close to you
but feeling really far away.

40:29.258 --> 40:30.859
You upset?

40:30.893 --> 40:32.093
No.

40:32.111 --> 40:34.196
I me...

40:34.230 --> 40:35.930
Do I like the idea of
not waking up next to you

40:35.948 --> 40:37.199
every day for a few months?

40:37.233 --> 40:38.600
Of course not.

40:38.618 --> 40:40.786
But you're right.

40:40.820 --> 40:42.404
I've spent so much
time talking about

40:42.438 --> 40:45.073
getting married,
and no time talking about

40:45.107 --> 40:47.909
what being a husband and
wife really means to us.

40:51.447 --> 40:53.965
What does it mean to you?

40:54.000 --> 40:56.051
Trust.

40:56.085 --> 41:00.138
Having a partner I know I will
always be honest with me.

41:00.173 --> 41:02.974
Who I know I will
always be honest with.

41:03.009 --> 41:04.593
What about you?

41:04.627 --> 41:06.928
Someone to accept me.

41:06.962 --> 41:08.430
All of me.

41:08.464 --> 41:11.483
Someone who I accept and adore.

41:11.517 --> 41:14.269
Neither of us said someone
who is with me every minute,

41:14.303 --> 41:16.771
or compromises their dreamsine.

41:16.773 --> 41:18.306
No.

41:18.324 --> 41:21.142
So... Then I guess
we're okay.

41:22.811 --> 41:26.281
Um... we will
switch off weekends.

41:26.315 --> 41:27.415
I'll come up or
you'll come down.

41:27.450 --> 41:28.583
And then I will come home,

41:28.618 --> 41:31.219
and then we will
finally get married.

41:33.539 --> 41:35.624
(School bell ringing)

41:35.658 --> 41:37.008
How you doing, buddy?

41:37.043 --> 41:38.760
Yeah. Good. But...

41:38.794 --> 41:40.828
How am I supposed to make
a car fly onstage

41:40.847 --> 41:43.682
in the auditorium?
(Laughs)

41:43.716 --> 41:45.333
You're really throwing yourself
into the musical, huh?

41:45.351 --> 41:46.852
I guess they're wrong

41:46.854 --> 41:50.639
when they say you
can't go home again.

41:50.673 --> 41:53.191
Well, it's not about being
back in high school again.

41:53.226 --> 41:54.476
I'm not interested in that.

41:54.510 --> 41:56.478
I guess it's just...

41:56.512 --> 41:59.197
Nice helping other people's
dreams come true.

41:59.232 --> 42:01.566
It's called being a teacher.

42:02.851 --> 42:04.202
I'm really gonna miss it.

42:05.488 --> 42:07.188
Wait, what do you mean?

42:07.206 --> 42:09.341
I'm leaving.

42:09.375 --> 42:10.825
Not-not for good,

42:10.859 --> 42:12.043
but for a few months.

42:12.078 --> 42:13.662
I'm going to Washington

42:13.696 --> 42:15.480
to fight to keep the as
alive in our schools.

42:15.515 --> 42:17.132
I figure if I don't
take a stand now,

42:17.166 --> 42:19.217
there won't be auditoriums
left to fly cars in.

42:19.252 --> 42:22.504
But, Mr. Shue, you can't just
leave the Glee Club like that,

42:22.538 --> 42:24.005
with no one in charge.
They need you.

42:24.039 --> 42:25.340
(Sigh)

42:25.374 --> 42:27.041
No, they need a leader.

42:29.729 --> 42:31.045
Someone who understands
how to win,

42:31.063 --> 42:32.647
but also understands that winning

42:32.682 --> 42:35.383
is not more important than
doing the right thing,

42:35.401 --> 42:37.235
or taking care of each other.

42:37.270 --> 42:39.521
Someone who's really good at
making kids' dreams come true.

42:39.555 --> 42:41.239
I spoke to Principal
Figgins about it,

42:41.274 --> 42:43.558
and since Glee Club
is not an actual class,

42:43.576 --> 42:46.161
we don't need a certified
teacher to run it.

42:46.195 --> 42:47.696
We just need an adult.

42:47.730 --> 42:50.665
Mr. Shue, I'm not an adult.
First of all,

42:50.700 --> 42:53.201
I think maybe it's time
you start calling me Will.

42:53.235 --> 42:55.403
And second how
you stood up to Sue.

42:55.421 --> 42:57.071
How you went out and found Ryder.

42:57.089 --> 42:58.873
You're ready.

42:58.907 --> 43:01.426
And if you're willing, then
I can promise you that

43:01.460 --> 43:03.011
there's no greater
joy in the world

43:03.045 --> 43:05.545
than helping a young boy
like you turn into a man.

43:08.006 --> 43:09.385
It's three months.

43:09.915 --> 43:10.887
So what are you doing?

43:12.027 --> 43:13.671
Will you take over the Glee Club?

